column2: If 4 weeks of quarantine has you running low on mental and emotional energy, may these words replenish you and give you comfort. #InLifeSheroes comes with reinforcements, before the weekend creeps up on us, to help us overcome the challenges of digesting this new normal. https://www.inlifesheroes.com/‚Ä¶/11-ways-enjoy-weekend-quara‚Ä¶

Always take care of yourself, whether you‚Äôre out getting supplies or at home doing your part to flatten the curve. At #InLifeSheroes, we are firm believers in self-care, especially in stressful times. Stay focused, stay positive and stay strong today and always. www.inlifesheroes.com

Now, more than ever, InLife remains committed to serving the Filipino people by protecting more lives financially. Last March 25, we started to make available InLife Wealth Assure Guaranteed Issue Offer (GIO). This allows one to get insured without undergoing medical exams and filling out lengthy applications. Send us a message to learn more  #ALifetimeForGood www.insularlife.com.ph/wealth-assure-gio

We thought our lives would go back to how they were today. But staying home is really the best way we can help stop COVID-19. If this has you feeling a little glum, come check out our Spotify playlist of 10 feel-good songs that are perfect for your morning routine. Power through! http://tiny.cc/Feel-goodSongs #ALifetimeForGood
We wish light to your home, clarity to your mind and a life filled with love, grace, and kindness. Happy Easter, everyone!üê∞ #ALifetimeForGood
May you have a blessed Holy Week and a joy-filled Easter!

This holy week, let us pray for healing, strength, and peace in our lives and in the world to overcome all the challenges we are faced with. May we all have a meaningful and blessed season of Lent. #ALifetimeForGood
We will continue to serve you online, through the extended lockdown, after the Holy Week. Stay safe and hopeful!

In times like this, it is best to keep our immune system strong. Taking small sips of water every 30 minutes leads to a healthy body, so make sure you have a water bottle with you anywhere you go, even if you‚Äôre at home. Stay hydrated, InLifers! #ALifetimeForGood

It looks like we‚Äôre going to be under community quarantine a little bit longer. Here‚Äôs a friendly reminder to do things you may have forgotten about living in our new normal. Stay safe and well at home!
Happy birthday is so yesterday! What are your other favorite 20-second lyrics that you sing along to when you wash your hands? Let us know in the comments down below! #ALifetimeForGood

column2: Treat yo' self! And the people you live with. These simple recipes submitted to us on #SheShares make use of ingredients that are most likely already in your pantry. If you're out, they're common enough to be in your go-to supermarket on your next supplies run. In the middle of a health crisis, find comfort and nutrition in good food. Stay healthy!  https://www.inlifesheroes.com/‚Ä¶/easy-healthy-recipes-quaran‚Ä¶ #InLifeSheroes

Relax and unwind with us with a movie! We're doing a Sheroes screening of Wonder Woman tomorrow night (Saturday) through Netflix Party!  Two easy steps to join: 1. Visit www.netflixparty.com to install Netflix Party  2. Go to bit.ly/sheroes-netflix-1 at 7PM tomorrow and click the NP icon next to the address bar Let's watch and chat the night away. See you there! #InLifeSheroes

Did you know that the act of learning actually makes us happier? The science backs it up! Check out these e-learning websites to lift your spirits and feed your mind while waiting out the lockdown. These sites have partnered with Ivy League schools and top universities worldwide, so you can be sure it‚Äôll be worth your time.  Create #ALifetimeForGood through knowledge and a positive attitude. edX - www.edx.org... Coursera - www.coursera.org Udemy - www.udemy.com Khan Academy - www.khanacademy.org

Three weeks into quarantine and still trying to master working from home? It really is quite difficult, especially when you have a family (or a dog!) around who you want to hang out with. The most important rule is to set boundaries. Keep these tips on how to achieve that in mind to help you focus and be more productive. And remember: stay away from your bed! üò¥ #ALifetimeForGood

column2: The current state of the world can get pretty stressful. Before you find yourself scrolling through an endless stream of coronavirus news on your phone, chips by your side, check out this entry from one of our #SheShares contributors on #InLifeSheroes. There are better ways to cope and, largely, it‚Äôs by taking good care of yourself.  https://www.inlifesheroes.com/‚Ä¶/self-care-during-a-covid-sc‚Ä¶

Got a lot on your mind lately? Tips, tricks, tools, techniques ‚Äî whatever it is, we'd love to hear it. Send it over to letstalk@inlifesheroes.com for a chance to be featured on #SheShares on www.inlifesheroes.com/she-shares. We could all use some fresh air on the internet right now. #InLifeSheroes

Since this virus broke out, we've been told many times by many people not to panic. But how exactly do you do that when there is so much uncertainty? One of our top Financial Advisors lets us in on what he tells close family and friends to do when it comes to managing their money these days. Keeping looking up, #ALifetimeForGood is still in the horizon.

We know how tough these times are. But we also know that the Filipino spirit is tougher‚Äîmore resilient than you think, more capable of rising above these obstacles. InLife is with each and everyone in hoping for better days to come. Things may be uncertain for now, but it won‚Äôt be like this forever. Aaahon tayo, Pilipinas. #ALifetimeForGood

column2: The best way to protect yourself, your family, and the frontliners in this fight against COVID-19 is to stay at home. As we all adjust to this new reality, we have extended further the grace period for premium payments to 90 days. If you need anything from InLife involving your policy, you may get in touch with us through the InLife Customer Portal bit.ly/inlife-cp

During this time of uncertainty, you can count on our unwavering support. InLife financial advisors are ready to talk to you to provide meaningful help and peace of mind when it comes to protecting your family and your finances. Just send us a message and we will be in touch! #ALifetimeForGood

See those stars? Explore them and see how they shine for you. This galaxy is a sign that the future is going to be as bright, no matter how difficult things may be right now.  #ALifetimeForGood #SolidFuture

Having a journal is not only a way to immortalize moments, but also a great reference for storytelling time with your children and grandchildren. Someday, they'lll ask about what happened during the pandemic‚Äîand by that time, if memories start to slip, this will come in handy. #ALifetimeForGood

There is some silver lining to this dark COVID cloud and that's being able to spend time with family, strengthening bonds, and deepening relationships. column2: Keep making memories that last a lifetime even while you're at home! Spending all this time with your kids might make you wonder a lot more about what what the world is going to be like and what their lives are going to be like many years from now. Have peace of mind when you know they'll be fine when you secure their future with a plan. Send us a message and let's preapre for it together  https://www.insularlife.com.ph/contact-us #ALifetimeForGood

The Insular Foundation, one of the first corporate foundations in the Philippines, has raised over P2M for our healthcare workers in the past 2 days through InLife employees, financial advisors, policyholders, and their close family & friends. Now, we are calling on the public for donations to purchase in bulk Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) for healthcare providers and first responders dealing with those impacted by the pandemic. Any amount you give will be matched 1:1, ...peso-for-peso, by the Foundation. You may send your donations through: ‚Ä¢ BPI - Account Name: Insular Foundation, Account No: 8841-0005-61 ‚Ä¢ Paypal - paypal.me/InsularFoundation and e-mail a screenshot of your confirmed transaction to info.foundation@insular.com.ph for an Official Receipt to be issued. Each of us doing a little bit really adds up and together, working as a community, we can overcome this health crisis. #EmpowermentForALifetime

With gyms closed and the outdoors off limits, #InLifeSheroes got in touch with an expert to give us the lowdown on how to get fit with no equipment and with limited space. Because being at home shouldn‚Äôt be the reason for a Shero to stop being super. Learn each exercise and get some pro tips here: https://www.inlifesheroes.com/articles/the-sheroes-workout

Being tested for the coronavirus and staying in the hospital can have significant financial consequences. Check your InLife policy if you have the I-Heal plan, a Lazada Premium Protect plan, or any individual life insurance plan with a hospitalization benefit (rider) attached to it. If you do, you may claim a daily hospitalization allowance if confinement is due to COVID-19 - based on your policy‚Äôs contract provisions. We want to help you focus on your recovery and relieve your loved ones of any more worry.

No matter what age you are, never take your health for granted. It's in times like these that we realize its importance. Start making it a priority today because losing it could really impact your finances. Talk to us and we'll help you come up with ways to better safeguard it. #ALifetimeForGood
